<paragraph id="8BA42669FFAEFFBDC6F457D8FD85F889" blockId="26.[151,1437,690,1833]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFAEFFBDC6F457D8FEB6F8A5" bold="true" box="[199,315,1771,1797]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFAEFFBDC4B057D8FC9EF8A5" authority="Liu &amp; Disney, 2022" authorityName="Liu &amp; Disney" authorityYear="2022" box="[643,787,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linzhiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFAEFFBDC4B057D8FC9EF8A5" box="[643,787,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">P. linzhiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFAEFFBDC52A57D8FCFCF8A5" bold="true" box="[793,881,1771,1797]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25C4700FFAEFFBDC52A57D8FCFCF8A5" box="[793,881,1771,1797]" pageId="26" pageNumber="227" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, it differs from the latter by shorter second section of costa and shape of sternite VI.
</paragraph>
